projects.description:
Currently working on implementation of Vertex (Global Tax Management Software Solution), that centralizes and automates the tax processes within Philips. The project includes multiple stakeholders (Global Tax, Business Process Owner Indirect Tax, Accenture, IT experts etc) and project planning for testing the various Philips goods flows (movement of the goods from one point to another) that are present in EMEA. Main activities of the project are:
- Identification of the potential risk areas in the process of Vertex Implementation;
- Process improvement;
- Testing of the tool in testing environment and feedback of the results to the IT Developers team;
- Collaborate closely with the IT Developers Team, Global Tax Transformation project team, Global Tax Team by sharing information, knowledge and experience.
Use: Daily CommCell, PDCA, SIPOC, RACI, KJ Methode, Clear Roles and responsibilities during meetings, E.L.M.O technique for effective meetings.

profile_positions.description:
Part of Tax Transformation Project Team in Philips. As certified Lean Advanced professional, I was working with diverse functions (Project Managers, Business Process Owners, Global Tax, Accenture, IT Experts etc.) in order to deliver in the most efficient and effective way the predefined project objectives for two implementation projects (Blueheart and Vertex) within Philips. My main responsibilities were to support the team from Process Improvement Perspective, by implementation of Lean Techniques and Methodologies in everyday work. 
Daily job involved:
-       Creation of CommCell in order to track the progress of the projects;
-       PDCA;
-	Supporting colleagues to have more efficient and effective meetings by implementing Lean techniques for effective meetings - TOR, E.L.M.O etc;
-	Mapping the current processes in the implementation projects using Lean and Six Sigma techniques;
-	Identify Waste in the processes;
-	Suggest Process Improvements;
-	Mapping the future state processes;
-	Write Implementation plan for the Blueheart project from Indirect tax perspective that should ensure on-time completition and meeting the defined test criteria for the migration.

Part of Center of Excellence, Accounting Operations. I was working closely with Indirect Tax Team in Infosys Lodz, Indirect Tax Managers from EMEA, Global Tax, Tax Authorities in EMEA markets, KPMG, E&Y, Internal and external auditors and Disbursements, in order to ensure implementation of standard work within Indirect Tax EMEA.
The role involved continuous interaction with these functions and making sure that all parties understand their role and responsibilities in the whole process by keeping the end goal of mind – On time and correct submission of the Indirect Tax reports for all EMEA Philips Organizations.
My main responsibilities included: 
-	Supervision and control on the Indirect Tax Process executed by Infosys Lodz, Infosys Pune and Country Market in EMEA; 
-	Supporting on their daily issues connected with Indirect Taxes by defining the problem, suggesting improvement, advising on the process steps to be taken and keeping track of the progress;
-	Identifying process improvement areas; 
-	First point of contact in case of audit from Tax Authorities in EMEA region;
-	First point of contact for Indirect Tax in case of internal audits;
-	Monthly calls with Global Tax and Country Markets in order to update each other on the current issues and the progress;
-	Mapping the Indirect tax processes per country;
-	Support on increasing the organizational knowledge for specific tax functional area by providing trainings, Tax do's & don’ts.
